{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbc476745-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3022"},"text":"§ 3022.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For the purpose of this subchapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc476746-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “comprehensive and coordinated system” means a system for providing all necessary supportive services, including nutrition services, in a manner designed to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc476747-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" facilitate accessibility to, and utilization of, all supportive services and nutrition services provided within the geographic area served by such system by any public or private agency or organization;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc476748-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" develop and make the most efficient use of supportive services and nutrition services in meeting the needs of older individuals;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc476749-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" use available resources efficiently and with a minimum of duplication; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc47674a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" encourage and assist public and private entities that have unrealized potential for meeting the service needs of older individuals to assist the older individuals on a voluntary basis.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc47674b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “education and training service” means a supportive service designed to assist older individuals to better cope with their economic, health, and personal needs through services such as consumer education, continuing education, health education, pre­retirement education, financial planning, and other education and training services which will advance the objectives of this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc47674c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “family caregiver” means an adult family member, or another individual, who is an informal provider of in-home and community care to an older individual or to an individual of any age with Alzheimer’s disease or a related disorder with neurological and organic brain dysfunction.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc47674d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “unit of general purpose local government” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc47674e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a political subdivision of the State whose authority is general and not limited to only one function or combination of related functions; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc47674f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3022/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an Indian tribal organization.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbc476750-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/73/tIII/s302"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–73, title III, § 302","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/478/tI/s103/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–478, title I, § 103(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1517"},"text":"92 Stat. 1517","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/115/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–115, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", (d), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1596"},"text":"95 Stat. 1596","children":[],"tail":", 1597; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/459/tIII/s302"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–459, title III, § 302","children":[],